NAME
    termcap(1)		- display the current termcap settings

SYNOPSIS
    termcap  [ type ]

DESCRIPTION
    Prints out the termcap capabilities as described in
    termcap(4). If "type" is not supplied then $TERM is
    used.

FILES
    /etc/termcap	terminal capabilities

SEE ALSO
    termcap(3), termcap(4)

BUGS
    Only a subset of the Unix termcap entries are recognized.

    The definitions for "k0" through "k5" were influenced by
    the unique case of running Minix on an IBM PC/AT.
